description.p:
As indicated in equation (5), the monitor compares the vertical angle θVG to a threshold angle to determine whether the patient is vertical (i.e. standing upright) or lying down:


if θVG≦45° then Torso State=0, the patient is upright  (5)


If the condition in equation (5) is met the patient is assumed to be upright, and their torso state, which is a numerical value equated to the patient's posture, is equal to 0. The patient is assumed to be lying down if the condition in equation (5) is not met, i.e. θVG>45 degrees. Their lying position is then determined from angles separating the two remaining vectors, as defined below.
